column10:
What are 'Hard' Scores?
Hard scores are the three categories of 'Push Feel', 'Wobble', and 'Sound' and inherent properties of the switch that stay consistent to the switch over time. Normally, these are a total of 70 points of the overall 100 used in the Overall Total Tab. These are separated out for people to see rankings based solely on performance metrics.
